2
00:01:31,339 --> 00:01:32,587
Delete!

3
00:01:33,649 --> 00:01:34,508
Delete!

4
00:01:42,818 --> 00:01:44,973
The average Japanese adult would say that.

5
00:01:44,998 --> 00:01:48,408
Teru Mikami was a child with a strong sense of justice.

6
00:01:48,752 --> 00:01:50,962
He was able to distinguish right from wrong

7
00:01:50,995 --> 00:01:52,606
better than any of his peers.

8
00:01:53,395 --> 00:01:55,650
And compared to the average Japanese person,

9
00:01:55,885 --> 00:01:58,851
Teru had been through and seen far worse miseries,

10
00:01:58,876 --> 00:02:00,282
and even witnessed death.

11
00:02:51,673 --> 00:02:52,401
His hat.

12
00:02:53,492 --> 00:02:54,179
Get it.

13
00:02:55,841 --> 00:02:59,193
In this world, there is only good and evil.

14
00:02:59,441 --> 00:03:04,920
That was one of the first universal truths I grasped
from observing the world around me when I was a child.

15
00:03:05,353 --> 00:03:10,374
Every human being, without exception, ends
up falling into one category or the other.

16
00:03:12,807 --> 00:03:15,459
Even those in innocent years of elementary school,

17
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:17,768
one could not escape that fact.

18
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:22,016
As class president, I strived to achieve
great things for my fellow students,

19
00:03:22,294 --> 00:03:24,294
but there were always enemies.

20
00:03:24,362 --> 00:03:25,995
Good against evil.

21
00:03:28,418 --> 00:03:30,860
No! Stop! Let go of me, please!

22
00:03:33,585 --> 00:03:35,165
Evil has to be confronted.

23
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,423
What do you want, nerd?

24
00:03:40,274 --> 00:03:43,694
There were times when it seemed
evil would triumph over good.

25
00:03:44,629 --> 00:03:46,562
But no matter what happened to me,

26
00:03:46,818 --> 00:03:48,863
I felt happy for one reason.

27
00:03:49,817 --> 00:03:51,170
Thank you, Teru.

28
00:03:52,951 --> 00:03:55,576
Hearing those words of gratitude from the victims

29
00:03:55,623 --> 00:03:58,230
made me want to save them again and again.

30
00:03:59,007 --> 00:04:02,757
For that reason, I never spared any effort.

31
00:04:03,431 --> 00:04:04,602
And in the end,

32
00:04:05,051 --> 00:04:08,047
I was able to stand up for my sense of justice.

33
00:04:12,151 --> 00:04:13,302
Does this bug you?

34
00:04:22,641 --> 00:04:25,679
But that was only true in the world of children.

35
00:04:30,962 --> 00:04:33,872
Middle school was another matter entirely.

36
00:04:34,563 --> 00:04:38,820
The more I confronted evil,
the more enemies I had to face.

37
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:42,934
Victims would become participants,

38
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,839
and even the people watching would be influenced by evil

39
00:04:45,864 --> 00:04:47,966
and become enemies themselves.

40
00:04:50,896 --> 00:04:54,446
But for justice to triumph, it requires action.

41
00:04:54,996 --> 00:04:59,161
So I realized, to serve justice, I had to delete evil.

42
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:04,240
The only person who understood
my hopes and remained my ally

43
00:05:04,265 --> 00:05:06,720
was the woman who raised me on her own.

44
00:05:07,173 --> 00:05:08,257
My mother.

45
00:05:08,651 --> 00:05:09,368
No.

46
00:05:09,785 --> 00:05:12,125
Rather, it used to be my mother.

47
00:05:15,707 --> 00:05:19,795
Teru, not everything in the world is
going to work the way you want it to.

48
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,406
You have to stop doing this.

49
00:05:22,431 --> 00:05:25,224
There's no reason for you to
suffer so much for your beliefs.

50
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:28,036
What do you think you're proving getting hurt like this?

51
00:05:28,785 --> 00:05:30,600
This is plain foolishness.

52
00:05:30,718 --> 00:05:32,762
You have to realize that somethings never change...

53
00:05:32,818 --> 00:05:34,540
My mother was wrong.

54
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,689
She didn't side with justice.

55
00:05:37,651 --> 00:05:40,528
She was one of those who deserved to be deleted.

56
00:05:41,651 --> 00:05:43,703
That was when the miracle happened.

57
00:05:47,043 --> 00:05:49,140
Four of the worst delinquents from my school

58
00:05:49,165 --> 00:05:51,707
lost control of their car while they were joyriding.

59
00:05:52,262 --> 00:05:53,423
They died instantly.

60
00:05:53,673 --> 00:05:55,911
One bystander was killed as well.

61
00:05:56,034 --> 00:05:58,844
That bystander was my mother.

62
00:05:59,973 --> 00:06:04,229
In one fell swoop, all the
people I resented had been deleted.

63
00:06:04,396 --> 00:06:06,609
At first, I was terrified.

64
00:06:06,818 --> 00:06:08,270
I couldn't stop shivering.

65
00:06:09,496 --> 00:06:11,438
But then it hit me.

66
00:06:11,884 --> 00:06:13,718
With these people out of the picture,

67
00:06:13,743 --> 00:06:16,090
how many others would benefit as a result?

68
00:06:16,574 --> 00:06:18,374
Clearly their victims were relieved.

69
00:06:18,399 --> 00:06:19,641
But beyond that.

70
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:22,935
Wouldn't everyone in my class be
happier now that they were gone?

71
00:06:24,462 --> 00:06:26,168
And sure enough, I was right.

72
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:29,376
Our classroom became a peaceful, joyful place.

73
00:06:31,718 --> 00:06:34,607
There will always the consequences for evil deeds.

74
00:06:34,665 --> 00:06:36,300
That is the way the world is.

75
00:06:36,873 --> 00:06:38,007
The way it should be.

76
00:06:40,862 --> 00:06:42,976
Evil must be deleted.

77
00:06:44,496 --> 00:06:46,095
Now then, let's see.

78
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,325
Are there any more problems with these records?

79
00:06:48,372 --> 00:06:49,016
No, they're fine.

80
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:50,320
With every passing year,

81
00:06:50,345 --> 00:06:53,108
my commitment to justice only grew stronger.

82
00:06:53,529 --> 00:06:57,448
I saw that there will always be
those who have no reason to exist.

83
00:06:57,763 --> 00:07:01,481
Those whose very existence is a threat to society.

84
00:07:01,828 --> 00:07:03,971
And the closer they grew to adulthood,

85
00:07:04,163 --> 00:07:06,736
the less likely was that they would ever reform.

86
00:07:07,462 --> 00:07:09,895
They could only be deleted.

87
00:07:14,729 --> 00:07:18,429
Mysteriously, every time I judged someone as evil,

88
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:20,623
they would soon be taken care of.

89
00:07:21,184 --> 00:07:22,420
Was it coincidence?

90
00:07:22,674 --> 00:07:24,130
Was I special somehow?

91
00:07:24,729 --> 00:07:27,352
In the end, it didn't matter.

92
00:07:27,829 --> 00:07:30,277
Divine judgment must be brought up evil.

93
00:07:30,585 --> 00:07:35,269
And if it isn't, then someone must
take it upon themselves to punish evil.

94
00:07:36,362 --> 00:07:38,562
That's why I became a prosecutor.

95
00:07:38,651 --> 00:07:42,317
It is the role of the prosecutor to
see that evil is brought to justice.

96
00:07:42,552 --> 00:07:44,298
It was an ideal job for me.

97
00:07:46,029 --> 00:07:47,162
And then...

98
00:07:49,107 --> 00:07:50,712
God came before me.

99
00:07:51,329 --> 00:07:53,506
Everything that had been happening around me

100
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:55,048
wasn't coincidence.

101
00:07:56,007 --> 00:07:57,903
It was divine justice.

102
00:07:59,673 --> 00:08:02,510
God had been watching me.

103
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:08,211
God had seen how I did not surrender to evil.

104
00:08:08,496 --> 00:08:12,272
He reached out his hand and
punished the evil people for me.

105
00:08:12,473 --> 00:08:17,147
Once I realized that, I started to frequent
places where God was bound to be watching.

106
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:18,900
And then it happened.

107
00:08:23,851 --> 00:08:27,284
God recognized me as I had always hoped!

108
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:31,770
Not only that, but he found me worthy
of sharing his power to eliminate evil!

109
00:08:35,485 --> 00:08:38,327
With this, it doesn't matter if I can't hear his voice.

110
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:42,095
I shall figure out what Kira wants and carry out his will.

111
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,796
Delete.

112
00:08:44,451 --> 00:08:45,344
Delete.

113
00:08:45,530 --> 00:08:46,522
Delete.

114
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,641
Delete.

115
00:08:48,174 --> 00:08:49,090
Delete.

116
00:08:49,229 --> 00:08:49,852
Delete.

